The actress Rita Wilson revealed she was diagnosed with invasive lobular carcinoma on Tuesday . 
  The 58-year-old actress said she underwent a double mastectomy and reconstructive surgery last week . 
  She took a leave of absence from Broadway play 'Fish in the Dark' earlier this month . 
  The mother-of-two said her first test for cancer came back negative but she was correctly diagnosed after seeking a second opinion . 
 